The '''Grapple on the Gridiron''' was a [[Collegiate wrestling|college]] [[wrestling]] dual meet held on November 14, 2015, in [[Iowa City]], [[Iowa]]. Historical rivals [[Oklahoma State Cowboys wrestling|Oklahoma State University]] and [[Iowa Hawkeyes wrestling|University of Iowa]]. A record<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackheartgoldpants.com/wrestling/2015/10/1/9422795/grapple-on-the-gridiron-tickets-on-sale-attendance-record-already|title=Grapple on the Gridiron Tickets on Sale; Attendance Record Already Broken|author=RossWB|work=Black Heart Gold Pants|accessdate=14 November 2015}}</ref> 42,287 fans attended the meet,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/IowaWRLive/status/665593221301448704|title=IowaWRLive on Twitter|work=Twitter|accessdate=14 November 2015}}</ref> held outdoors at the [[Kinnick Stadium]], normally the home of [[Iowa Hawkeyes football|Iowa's football program]]. The meet marked the first time two college teams wrestled in a football stadium <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thepredicament.com/2015/08/grapple-on-the-gridiron-set-for-iowa-vs-okie-state/|title=Grapple on the Gridiron set for Iowa vs. Okie State|accessdate=8 December 2015}}</ref> and the first time a NCAA Division I football stadium had hosted wrestling match.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kimt.com/2015/11/15/grapple-on-the-gridiron-sets-ncaa-wrestling-attendance-record/|title="Grapple on the Gridiron" sets NCAA wrestling attendance record|accessdate=8 December 2015}}</ref>
